","type":"application/javascript","module-type":"parser"},"$:/plugins/rimir/frontmatter/readme":{"title":"$:/plugins/rimir/frontmatter/readme","text":"! Frontmatter

Store tiddler metadata as YAML frontmatter directly inside `.md` files — no `.meta` sidecar needed.

!! How it works

Set a tiddler's type to `text/x-frontmattered-markdown`. On save, the tiddler is written as a single `.md` file with YAML frontmatter:

```
---
title: My Tiddler
tags:
  - documentation
  - example
created: "20260330120000000"
modified: "20260330120000000"
type: text/x-frontmattered-markdown
---

# Markdown content here
```

Existing `text/x-markdown` tiddlers are unaffected and continue to use `.meta` sidecars.

!! Features

* YAML frontmatter with `---` delimiters
* Tags and list fields serialized as YAML arrays
* Automatic cleanup of orphaned `.meta` files when migrating
* Works with filesystem-watcher for live external edits
* Renders identically to regular markdown tiddlers

!! Prerequisites

* TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+ (Node.js server edition)
* The official `tiddlywiki/markdown` plugin (for rendering)
